<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Fast Radio Bursts Analogy</title>
  <style>
    /* Simple text-only styling */
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #fff;
      color: #000;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 2em;
    }
    /* Initially hide the secret message */
    #secret {
      opacity: 0;
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 1em;
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
      // After 1 second, show the secret message (simulate the burst)
      setTimeout(function() {
        var secret = document.getElementById('secret');
        secret.style.opacity = 1;
        // After 1.5 seconds, hide the message again
        setTimeout(function() {
          secret.style.opacity = 0;
        }, 1500);
      }, 1000);
    });
  </script>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to the FRB Analogy</h1>
  <p>Keep an eye on the pageâ€”sometimes, you might catch a fleeting burst of information.</p>
  <div id="secret">Secret Message: FRB Detected!</div>
  <p>This brief flash represents the transient nature of fast radio bursts.</p>
</body>
